  <title>MD-Conjugate-Cams</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Conjugate Cams<keyword>Definition</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>Conjugate-Cams</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Body Text2-Note"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Conjugate-Cam definition</text><text styleclass="Interface">: </text>(<text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-size:10pt;">MechDesigner</text>) a minimum of two(2) <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">2D-Cams</text> on one <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>, each in contact with a different <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Cam-follower Roller</text> that is on one(1) different <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">By definition: the two 2D-Cams move together with one motion, and the two Cam-Follower move together with a different motion.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Interface">Conjugate-Cam definition:</text> (formal (Norton) comprise a pair of cams on a common shaft that drive a pair of followers arranged on a common lever or slider that maintain a fixed distance or angle between the (flat) follower surfaces or (roller) center-lines. </para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Popup Box">See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-ConjugateCam-FB" styleclass="Popup Box">Machine-Elements menu &gt; Add Conjugate Cam FB</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
